- Neighborhood type (e.g., urban, suburban, rural) is used as a categorization, not necessarily implying a specific geographic or socioeconomic characteristic;
- Average income and population are proxies for the socioeconomic status of the neighborhoods;
- Cumulative totals imply adding up values as you move from one row to the next within each neighborhood type group.

sql:
SELECT SUM(total_crimes) AS total_crimes_2022
FROM crime_stats
WHERE year = 2022;
